  "prompt": "I got 753 rank in Aiims and I have not attended to 1 at counseling. will I am eligible for second and third counseling?",
  "response": "In general, for AIIMS and similar medical entrance counseling processes in India, candidates who do not attend the first round of counseling typically lose their chance in that round but may still be eligible for subsequent rounds. However, eligibility can depend on various factors, including specific rules set by the examination conducting bodies for that year.\n\nTo ensure accurate information regarding your eligibility for the second and third rounds of counseling, it is crucial to check the official AIIMS counseling guidelines for the year you are applying, as rules may vary from year to year. Additionally, you might want to reach out to the official helpdesk or support services for AIIMS counseling for clarification based on your specific situation.",
